name: Marriott Marquis Washington DC
directions:
Elevator
Take elevator down one floor from lobby area to M1. Turn left out of the elevator and left again. Straight back you'll see water fountains and the gender neutral accessible single stall "Family Restroom" is just past the men's room.
comment: Likely to be occupied when the hotel is busy.

name: First Unitarian Church
directions: Turn right after entering,  go down 2 steps, multi-stall on left, single stall with changing table on right.
comment: Only open 10am-2pm Mon-Thurs.   Church hours on Sunday.

name: Barnes-Jewish Hospital
directions: I used this bathroom when my mom was in surgery. I'm not there now, so I apologize if directions are slightly off. This bathroom was single stall and I'm 98% sure it was gender neutral. It is down the hall from the elevators, last door before the little patient cubicles with curtains. The door is on the left. It is ADA accessible.

name: Santa Fe College
directions: A part of building M, across from building L.
comment: It's a part of the school, so any students that want a place to feel comfortable can come to this restroom.

name: Lazy Daisy's
directions: Down the stairs. (Stair door towards the middle on the left hand side.)
comment: Bathrooms have pictures of cows and are labeled "Gender Moo-tral."

name: Lazy Daisy's
directions: Down the stairs. (Stair door towards the middle on the left hand side.)
comment: Bathrooms have pictures of cows and are labeled "Gender Moo-tral."

name: J. Foster Watkins Academic Building, Landrum Education Dr, Oakwood, GA 30566, USA
directions: Along the back wall behind the ACTT center there are two single person, unisex and accessible restrooms. There are two others in the building, but those are designated for faculty and staff.

name: Simply Coffeehouse & Eatery
directions: If you walk to the seating in the back, there's two single stall gender neutral restrooms off to the right.

name: Port orchard library
directions: In the back of the library
comment: Open to anyone, two gender neutral restrooms, need a key to access

name: Columbia City Hall
directions: The restroom is on the mezzanine of the older side of the building. The elevator on the older part of the building goes to that level.

name: 1st and Collins Starbucks
comment: the left room has a urinal and the right does not, but they are both marked as unisex bathrooms. Single stall

name: Leslie J. Savage Library - Western State Colorado University
directions: 3rd floor, room 310.
comment: Available to anyone, during all open hours. It's a single-person, private bathroom. There is an elevator, but the door and bathroom themselves are kind of small, so a wheelchair may not fit.

name: Center for Care and Discovery
directions: Both east and west lobbies have gender neutral restrooms, as well as when you get into the hospital itself.
comment: The attached Starbucks and Qdoba DO NOT have gender neutral restrooms.

name: Kowalski's Market
directions: When you walk in, make a right and the restroom is down a small hall past the drink coolers.
comment: You don't have to be a paying customer to use this restroom and you can grab a free cup of coffee while you're in!

name: Kowalski's Market
directions: When you walk in, make a right and the restroom is down a small hall past the drink coolers.
comment: You don't have to be a paying customer to use this restroom and you can grab a free cup of coffee while you're in!

name: Celebration Cinema North
comment: They are past the ticket counter I think.

name: Holiday
directions: When you enter, the restroom is all the way to the left.
comment: You don't have to be a paying customer to use this restroom.

name: Great Wolf Lodge
directions: Main floor, across from the gift shop. From the main entrance, take a right at Starbucks, it is just down the hall on your right.
comment: So chaotic in here, nobody will notice you!

name: Chapterhouse Cafe & Gallery
directions: Single stall, gender neutral, in the middle room

name: EF Center Boston
directions: On the ground floor, in the cafe on the right as you come through the main entrance, keep walking past the bar and turn left.
comment: No need to buy anything! There are six or so single stall unisex restrooms.

name: AMC Danbury
directions:
On the 5-16 side, go all the way down to the end of the hall and go to the right. Right before theatre 13 is a family/unisex restroom. 

If you don't want to use the family restroom, the restrooms on that end of the theatre (women's by 15, men's by 12) are used a lot less compared to the lobby restrooms.
comment: You do need a ticket to get down that hall

name: AMC Danbury
directions:
On the 5-16 side, go all the way down to the end of the hall and go to the right. Right before theatre 13 is a family/unisex restroom. 

If you don't want to use the family restroom, the restrooms on that end of the theatre (women's by 15, men's by 12) are used a lot less compared to the lobby restrooms.
comment: You do need a ticket to get down that hall

name: Robert Lee Moore Hall (math/physics/astronomy building)
directions: Take the elevator to the second floor. Walk in the opposite direction of the double doors down the left fork of the short hallway (you should see a sign that says "Laser in use", walk under it). The bathroom is at the end of the hallway to the left!

name: Buggytown Sub Shop
directions: To the left as you come in. Restrooms are marked men/women but each is a single toilet and sink.
comment: Restrooms are too small to be wheelchair accessible and in fact the restaurant itself is up a few steps to enter.

name: Target
directions: Second floor to the left at the top of the escalator.
comment: Two non gendered single occupancy restrooms. Generally kept quite clean!

name: School of The Art Institute of Chicago - Sharp Building
directions: Take elevator to the 3rd floor, exit to your left, then make another left at the very next hallway. You'll see all of the bathrooms, the two gendered bathrooms are the first two doors and the gender nuetral single stall is next.
comment: Since it's in the school you'll generally have to have a reason to be there (ie. guest lecturer, student or family visiting, attending an even or exhibition etc.) as well as get a temporary visitor's pass but if you're visiting the school for some reason just know there are gender neutral bathrooms here.

name: Elderberry's
directions: Straight back, to right.
comment: Paying customers.

name: University of Oregon Clinical Services Bldg
directions: 1st Floor all gender restroom by north entrance/exit

name: Providence Regional Medical Center Everett - Pacific Campus
directions: 2 unisex private stalls on first floor of main hospital building. One is visible from the back parking lot entrance, the other is right next to public elevators.
comment: The restroom by the main entrance on the main floor is a gendered multistall restroom. Go up one floor to the first floor to find the unisex private stalls. Building is only open to public 9 am to 7 pm. In my experience staff here is very friendly and trained to understand trans folks needs

name: University of Oregon Clinical Services Building
directions: Restroom is on first floor, by the Kitchen. Walk around the hallways as if to exit on the north side, you'll see it

name: University of Oregon Clinical Services Building
directions: Restroom is on first floor, by the Kitchen. Walk around the hallways as if to exit on the north side, you'll see it

name: Killingsworth Dynasty
directions: Two gender neutral bathrooms, both open. As you approach the bathrooms, the one on the left is the more traditional "male" bathroom with a stall and a urinal. The one on the right is the more traditional "female" bathroom with stalls. Both are labeled as gender neutral.
comment: Unsure about paying customer policy. It's a bar, so I'm sure it depends on how full it is.

name: Integrated science complex
directions: 2nd floor, left near the bio labs

name: Knight Library
directions: First/ground floor near stairwell.

name: Hesburgh library
directions: 10th floor, behind the elevators

name: Springfield Little Theatre
directions: Third floor. Labeled as women's but single influential

name: Prince Lucien Campbell Hall
directions: 8th and 9th Floors outside elevator

name: Sabino Canyon
directions: Family restroom outside to the right of the visitors center/gift shop, near other bathrooms.
comment: If you park in the lot they may require a $5 parking pass.

name: Jb's Mongolian Grill
directions: Six individual stalls total, 1 accessible
comment: try the food, it is delicious

name: Heavenly Bite bake & cafe
directions: To the right of the counter. 2 single use washrooms. Very polite staff.

name: Starbucks Vineyard Town Center
directions: In the far righthand corner, past the coffee pickup bar

name: Thinker Toys
directions: Straight back from front door, through the purple doorway, purple door on the left (not marked as a restroom)
comment: Almost accessible, the doorways are wide enough & there are no stairs but sometimes there are boxes in the hallway. You can ask an employee to move them if necessary to pass with a mobility device and tell the employee to call Holly if there are any questions about that.

name: Trident Booksellers and Cafe
directions: Downstairs bathrooms are gender neutral, upstairs is gendered.

name: Trident Booksellers and Cafe
directions: Downstairs bathrooms are gender neutral but upstairs is gendered.

name: Kohl's
directions: Family restroom is in the back of the store on the right side- between the cards and baby section.

name: Dubois County Herald
directions: Upstairs in the newsroom
comment: Just say you have a meeting with a reporter

name: Kitt Central
directions: When you go in the front door you can either ask the people at the front desk where the bathroom is or go down the stairs and right next to the kitchen.
comment: There are two rooms right next to each other. Both are gender neutral. This is a residence hall so there could be a lot of people in the common room.

name: Dunkin' Donuts
directions: Inside, by rear entrance.

name: Black Kite Coffee
directions: Back of coffee shop
comment: It's a small, local coffee shop so if possible get yourself some delicious brew but they are empathetic so if you need just the bathroom they'll understand.

name: University of New Haven Dental Clinic
directions: When you enter, it is left down the corridor and then right and it's on your right.
comment: It is a clinic but they shouldn't bother you.

name: Salem Public Library
directions: Currently children's department is gender neutral, expect all to be by end of 2017. Ask at desk to be let into bathroom.
comment: Staff is friendly. Children's librarian office is near bathroom. Children's librarian is an ally- find her if anyone gives you a problem.

name: Salem Public Library
directions: Currently children's department is gender neutral, expect all to be by end of 2017. Ask at desk to be let into bathroom.
comment: Staff is friendly. Children's librarian office is near bathroom. Children's librarian is an ally- find her if anyone gives you a problem.

name: Commonplace Coffeehouse and Roastery
directions: At the end of the large hallway is the coffee shop. It's a bit hard to locate.
comment: The environment is very friendly. The staff won't mind using the restroom.

name: The Nook Cafe
directions: Straight back to the left.

name: Circus Coffee House
directions: Down the stairs and around the corner to the right.

name: Regina Hospital
directions: Through the main entrance which is right next to the ED entrance.  As you walk in the restrooms are to your left about 20 feet.  2 unisex rooms also meeting ADA standards
comment: You don't have to be a patient or anything, open to the public.

name: Matnas Tverya
directions: Community center. Bathrooms are available whenever the location is open. Single stalls

name: Abraham Lincoln high school
directions: First floor of the main building

name: WKU Glasgow Campus
directions: Second floor, at the end of the hallway, by the stairwell

name: Cafe Hapina
directions: Bathroom is easy to find
comment: Friendly space. Good food. Lgbt friendly. Single bathroom

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back of the cafe around a corner
comment: Can just walk in; do not have to be a customer

name: Doobie's Place
comment: Lgbt friendly cafe. The bathroom ain't great, but it's safe.

name: Akron General Medical Center - Ambulatory Care Center
directions: ACC is the distinct glass building in the medical center. Restrooms located on the 4th Floor, Bariatics/Surgery department. Take the elevator to 4, turn right off the elevator, and then right again near Reception. Go straight for about thirty feet- two private restrooms are on the left.

name: Barnard College, Barnard Hall
directions: Straight through the gates and into barnard hall, left and its immediately on the right in an enclove.

name: Coffee Mob
comment: For customers only, small space, might need to buy a drink

name: Plaza Emporium
directions: Take the rihht most door as you enter. There are two single stall gender neutral restrooms in the back of the dining area.
comment: The buffet side only has gendered restrooms and you have to pay to get in on that side.

name: Gettysburg College
directions: Single stall near C.U.B entrance that has the ATM. Go through that entrance, up 3 or 4 steps, into the large main lobby. The bathroom is in the corner to the left in the big lobby.
comment: Open to the public

name: Costa Coffee
directions: Back of the store
comment: Possibly need to pay - haven't checked

name: La Colombe Coffee Shop
directions: Behind an unmarked door near the coffee bar. It's a single toilet and no key is needed.
comment: Staff are friendly.

name: The Lavender Clinic
directions: Entrance to The Lavender Clinic is just outside parking garage entrance, in the Hawaii Dental Association building.
comment: This is the main location for Hawaii state's only Transgender-oriented healthcare specialty and primary care clinic. All are welcomed.

name: Heine Brothers Chenoweth Lane
directions: To the right of the bar in hallway (if you're looking at the menu)
comment: Friendly store, no questions asked. You don't have to be a customer. Baby changing stations in both restrooms. Large locking single gender restrooms

name: Moore College of Art and Design
directions: Stahl Hall, by the elevators
comment: You need to check in with security at the front desk. Stahl hall is where the administrative offices are.

name: Apple University Park Mall
directions: Through the large metal door at the back of the store.
comment: This bathroom IS for customer/store use. You do not have to purchase something.

name: New Seasons Lombard
directions: As you enter walk toward the bakery.  The restroom is near the seating area at the front of the bakery.

name: Roots Market
directions: On the back wall of the store, right past the customer service desk.
comment: Proprietors don't require purchase to use restroom.

name: JCCC
directions: First floor library bathroom by East entrance.

name: Jill's Place
directions: In the back by the kitchen
comment: LGBT owned restaurant. 1 single stall for women, and one for anybody.

name: Target
directions: To the left when you enter the store.
comment: There are multi-stall bathrooms and family bathrooms.

name: Public Restrooms
directions: At the far end of the municipal parking lot, which has First Bank on one side and the Southwest Harbor Police Department on the other. One-story grey building with signs.
comment: Available to all; 24/7

name: Gettysburg National Military Park Museum and Visitor Center
directions: Single stall Family Bathrooms available near the main and group entrances
comment: Open to the public

name: Mama Mia Restaurant
directions: From the street entrance, walk straight in, past the koi pond and kids corner and turn left

name: Market Hotel
directions: Second floor, marked with photos of urinals or toilets

name: University of winchester
directions: Through the side door turn right down the corridor
